<body>
    <header>
        Predictive Analysis for Traffic Flow & Congestion Management
    </header>
    
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>Traffic congestion is a growing issue in urban areas, leading to increased travel times, fuel consumption, and pollution. This project aims to develop a predictive analytics system using machine learning techniques to anticipate congestion patterns and improve traffic management.</p>
        
        <h2>Problem Statement</h2>
        <p>Current traffic management relies on reactive measures rather than predictive analytics. This project will provide authorities with real-time congestion forecasts, enabling proactive decision-making for better traffic control and route optimization.</p>
        
        <h2>Research Methodology</h2>
        <p>We use real-time data sources like GPS tracking, road sensors, and CCTV cameras. Machine learning models such as Random Forest and LSTM will be implemented for accurate traffic prediction.</p>
        
        <h2>System Architecture</h2>
        <p>The system consists of a data collection layer, a machine learning processing unit, and a visualization dashboard to provide real-time traffic insights.</p>
